//float s=2.5f % 2; //0.5 --commented ----> how is this 0.5 comes as result?
  float s=2.5%2; //0.5
	float r=2.5f / 2; //1.25
	System.out.println(r);
  System.out.println(s);
   
// here we are assigning the value  to s is s =2.5%2 . 2.5 is the float and 2 is integer when you perform the arithmetic operations
with mixed types like this java automatically promotes the integer to float for the operation. so 2 is coverted to 2.0
and will get the result in float.

